cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to better comprehend procedural text. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves the use of neural networks and deep learning, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The authors also mention the use of biasing towards more plausible predictions, which could fall under cs.LG (Learning). The paper also involves information retrieval techniques to identify subsequent steps, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the authors mention the use of a new model, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
